code:

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['variety'])['yield'].mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the average yield of each variety?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Average Yield')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', kde=True, hue='site', multiple='stack', palette='bright')
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Yield: {:.2f}'.format(data['yield'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield across all sites?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='yield', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['site'] = data['site'].astype('category')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="site", y="yield", data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Site', ylabel='Yield')
    plt.title('What is the yield distribution at each site?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
